Appointment Management

Give your portal users a personalized experience in scheduling appointments. Configure the My Appointments component in the Experience Builder to provide your portal users with options for scheduling in-person, phone, or video appointments.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited editions where Financial Services Cloud license is enabled

Create and Assign a Permission Set
Create and assign a permission set for portal users to grant the license and permissions they need to schedule and manage appointments in the Financial Services Client Portal.

Set Up a Sharing Set for Service Appointment Records
Give your portal users access to the Service Appointment records using a sharing set. A sharing set grants portal users access to a record associated with an account or contact that matches the userâ€™s account or contact.

Update Sharing Settings for Portal Users
Use organization-wide default sharing settings to set the baseline external access for Salesforce Scheduler records.

Configure the Inbound Appointment Flow
Clone and activate the new inbound appointment flow and add it to your Experience Cloud Portal to let portal users schedule new appointments.

Activate Service Territory Data Integration Rule
Ensure that service appointments scheduled by portal users are routed to appropriate teams or individuals within specific regions or territories.

Manage Business Information for Appointment Booking
Configure business information related to service locations, resources, skills, topics, and appointment templates to provide a personalized experience for portal users in scheduling appointments.

Set Up Video Appointments
Let portal users book video appointments with service resources.
title: Personalizing Portal User Experience with Appointment Management
